        "content": "<p>Hey all! I've been trying to use a lot of <code>let</code>s in my code for clarity, but it feels like it always ends up being a pain to do so. For example, look at this mwe:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">true</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">begin</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">let</span> <span class=\"n\">some_fun</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">λ</span> <span class=\"n\">asda</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">ite</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">asda</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">23</span> <span class=\"bp\">∨</span> <span class=\"n\">asda</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">420</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"mi\">123</span> <span class=\"mi\">456</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">suffices</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">some_fun</span> <span class=\"mi\">23</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">some_fun</span> <span class=\"mi\">420</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">trivial</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">simp</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">some_fun</span><span class=\"o\">],</span> <span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>For some reason, I need both <code>simp</code>s; if I try just one, it pretty much just unfolds <code>some_fun</code> and then gives up. Is this something one of the hidden <code>simp</code> parameters can solve?</p>",
